            "title": "Unit 1: Foundational Elements for Working Together",
            "content": [
                {
                    "id": 0,
                    "title" : "Introduction",
                    "blocks":[
                        {
                            "id":0,
                            "type":"ImageText",
                            "details":
                                {
                                    "layout":"left",
                                    "text":"This unit explores some foundational elements we use when supporting another student’s learning.",
                                    "image":"https://courses.ecampus.oregonstate.edu/oer/peer-ed/content/assets/xJirH-Iq04RVptMQ_yOJuJFpHempJ-JpZ.jpg",
                                    "alt": "People having a conversation in a hallway"
                                }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":1,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"Before you begin Unit 1, please click on the \"Unit 1 Reflection Guide\" link below to download/print a note-taking sheet."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":2,
                            "type":"DownloadBox",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"Click the button to download and print the Unit 1 Reflection Guide",
                                "link":"http://www.google.com/"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":3,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"Remember, this is a tool for your learning and a resource you can use as you continue to work as a peer educator. Additionally, depending on your training format, your supervisor may ask you to show or submit your reflection notes as a confirmation that you’ve done the work."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":4,
                            "type":"Divider",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "format":"number",
                                "character":"1"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":5,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"Many people assume that the key elements of successful peer education are based on knowledge of how to teach and the subject matter itself. While those are important, and we will talk more about those in the following units, the base of successful support also has to do with the relationship you build together."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":6,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"If you think back to some of the experiences you’ve had that felt most “helpful” - you may notice the importance of feeling listened to and feeling like the other person cares about your success. In contrast, perhaps you can remember a time when you didn’t feel listened to or supported."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":7,
                            "type":"Divider",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "format":"number",
                                "character":"2"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":8,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"In her 1999 study, researcher Marcia Baxter Magolda asked students to “describe teaching environments that they found helpful in promoting their learning.” She discovered as a theme that students appreciated when teachers showed:"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":9,
                            "type":"CardReveal",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "revealText": "Click here to reveal the results",
                                "text":"\"caring attitude towards students\"",
                                "textTwo":"\"condern for the students\""
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":10,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"While this looked different from student to student - the theme still emerged as an important element of her research and has been found in subsequent studies."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":11,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"In 2000, researcher Geneva Gay demonstrated that a caring relationship can impact the outcomes of learning. Her research indicated that:"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":12,
                            "type":"CardReveal",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "revealText": "Click here to see what the research indicated",
                                "text":"Caring makes people more willing to participate",
                                "textTwo":"Caring encourages achievement",
                                "textThree":"Caring prompts student effort and hard work"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":13,
                            "type":"TaskBlock",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "color":"rgb(255, 88, 88)",
                                "image":"https://courses.ecampus.oregonstate.edu/oer/peer-ed/content/assets/F_BhZE2fdDseZF98_9AHPqZanuHArRVCb.png",
                                "text":"Reflection #1 - Fill out this section on your Notes Sheet"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":14,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"A caring and supportive interaction can also enhance students’ sense of belonging at the institution, which is then magnified by the new levels of success they experience. This sets a positive cycle in motion, where care and accomplishment mutually reinforce student success."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":15,
                            "type":"Text",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "text":"With that in mind, the first unit “Foundational Elements for Working Together” focuses on the interpersonal and communication-based elements that we use when working with and supporting another student’s learning."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":16,
                            "type":"Divider",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "format":"number",
                                "character":"3"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":17,
                            "type":"SubjectBlock",
                            "details":
                            {
                                "backgroundType": "none",
                                "align": "left",
                                "text":"For Unit 1, we have chosen five important topics that provide the foundation for working with another person."
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id":18,
                            "type":"ImageBullets",
                            "details":
                            [
                                {
